    "chemicalDescription": [
      "r-(s-Escherichia Coli Thioredoxin-1 Heptapeptide-44 Hexapeptide-40 Oligopeptide-165 sh-Polypeptide-122) is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from r-Escherichia Coli Thioredoxin-1, Heptapeptide-44, Hexapeptide-40, Oligopeptide-165 and sh-Polypeptide-122. The fusion peptide contains 284 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acid."
    ],
